title: Pinoy makes it to top 7 of 'X Factor Australia'
text:
Pinoy makes it to top 7 of 'X Factor Australia' ABS-CBNnews.com Posted at 10/20/2015 5:53 PM Cyrus Villanueva performs a Lenny Kravitz song for this week's rock & roll theme. Photo: The X Factor Australia 
MANILA - Despite his performance that had judges divided , Filipino-Australian singer Cyrus Villanueva has made it to the top 7 of “The X Factor Australia, it was revealed Tuesday. 
The 19-year-old Villanueva earned enough votes to move on to the next round along with other contestants Natalie Conway, Michaela Barano, Louise Adams, Big T (Tangaroa Te Tai), Mahalia Simpson and Jess & Matt. 
Boy group In Stereo, meanwhile, were eliminated. 
For the competition’s rock-themed episode, Villanueva, who is mentored by American rock icon Chris Isaak, performed Lenny Kravitz’“It Ain’t Over Til It’s Over.” 
While his rendition impressed his coach, it did not sit well with the other judges James Blunt and Guy Sebastian. The two thought that the song choice did not fall within the week’s theme.
